[SN]TITLE[SN]
EU referendum: Wrightbus owner backed Leave vote over immigration

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The founder of bus-maker Wrightbus has said the main reason he backed a Leave vote in the EU referendum was over immigration.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
28 June 2016 Last updated at 22:14 BST
William Wright also said the fall in the pound would help his business. However, another business described the decision to leave the EU as a "kick in the back of the legs".
BBC News NI's business correspondent Julian O'Neill reports.
